rComments: He explains the content really well and gives great examples that reflect what we are tested on. Assignments are quite easy as are the tests. One of the best professors I have had so far.
Probably the best professor I have had at uOttawa. He uses a lot of examples to teach content and his exams/assignments are very easy. Only problem I have is the exams are little too easy.
Boring teacher with meandering, hard to follow lectures. Assignments better reflect the textbook than the class. Do not recommend this class or this professor.

He is an excellent professor. He makes C++ easy to understand with many useful examples. The assignments were straightforward to get perfect on. You need to show up at lectures and labs but that's all you need to pass.

Amir is the sweetest prof ever, he runs this class really well! Assignments were really easy and helpful to confirm my programming knowledge. Plenty of time to do assignments, but beware of starting them last minute. He is very helpful if you have questions in advance. Answer questions in class and you just might land some bonus points for the exam
One of the best prof who really made a hard course easier.

I was worried going into this course, but Professor Amir made everything so easy to understand. He has plenty of examples and demos for C++ concepts that were introduced. The assignments/project were pretty easy to get a good grade on. He's easily one of the most approachable and caring profs I've had.

He is one of the best profs I have ever had. The assignments are super doable and the exams were literally what he thought in class. C++ is not an easy language but he really tries to simplify it so his students understand.

Though this was his first time teaching, he was really good. His lecture note is very clear and he is always able to give amazing examples of how the material is used. Assignment and Midterm feedback was always very precise and useful. He cares very much for his students.
